{"post_content":"<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 1: Introduction to Git &amp; Version Control<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What is Git? Why use it?<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>How Git compares to other version control systems<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Key concepts: Repository, commits, branches, merge<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 2: Setting Up Git<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Installing Git (Windows, macOS, Linux)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Configuring Git (<code>git config<\/code>, global vs. local settings)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Setting up SSH keys for GitHub\/GitLab<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Creating your first Git repository<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 3: Git Basics \u2013 Working with Repositories<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Initializing a repository (<code>git init<\/code>)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Cloning a repository (<code>git clone<\/code>)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Staging changes (<code>git add<\/code>)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Committing changes (<code>git commit<\/code>)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Viewing history (<code>git log<\/code>, <code>git show<\/code>)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Making and tracking changes in Git<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 4: Branching &amp; Merging<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Understanding Git branches (<code>git branch<\/code>)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Switching branches (<code>git checkout<\/code>, <code>git switch<\/code>)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Merging changes (<code>git merge<\/code>)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Fast-forward vs. three-way merges<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Resolving merge conflicts<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Creating and merging branches<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Break \u2013 30 minutes<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 5: Remote Repositories &amp; Collaboration<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Working with remote repositories (<code>git remote add<\/code>, <code>git fetch<\/code>)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Pushing and pulling changes (<code>git push<\/code>, <code>git pull<\/code>)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Forking and cloning repositories<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Working with GitHub\/GitLab<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Collaborating with Git using remote repositories<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 6: Git Undo &amp; Rewriting History<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Reverting changes (<code>git checkout<\/code>, <code>git restore<\/code>)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Undoing commits (<code>git reset<\/code>, <code>git revert<\/code>)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Working with <strong>stash<\/strong> (<code>git stash<\/code>)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Amending commits (<code>git commit --amend<\/code>)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Undoing changes and managing commit history<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 7: Git Best Practices &amp; Workflows<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Best practices for commit messages<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Feature branching, Git Flow, and trunk-based development<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Handling large repositories and optimizing performance<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Using <code>.gitignore<\/code> effectively<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Applying best practices in a real-world Git workflow<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"\/>\n<!-- \/wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Final Exercise &amp; Q&amp;A<\/strong><\/h2>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Open Q&amp;A session<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hands-on: <strong>Team collaboration scenario with Git workflows<\/strong><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->","post_type":"training","post_status":"publish","post_name":"git-essentials","post_title":"Git Essentials","post_password":"","post_date":"2025-03-12 15:16:36","post_date_gmt":"2025-03-12 15:16:36","post_excerpt":"This hands-on 1-day (7-hour) training provides a solid foundation in Git, the most widely used version control system. You will learn essential Git commands, workflows, branching strategies, and best practices for efficient collaboration in software development.","post_parent":null,"author":"admin","meta":{"_aioseo_description":[null],"_aioseo_keywords":["a:0:{}"],"_aioseo_og_article_section":[""],"_aioseo_og_article_tags":["a:0:{}"],"_aioseo_og_description":[null],"_aioseo_og_title":[null],"_aioseo_title":[null],"_aioseo_twitter_description":[null],"_aioseo_twitter_title":[null],"_edit_last":"admin","audience":["<ul>\r\n<li>Developers, DevOps engineers, and system administrators<\/li>\r\n<li>IT professionals working with version-controlled projects<\/li>\r\n<li>Anyone new to Git or looking to improve their workflow<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>"],"duration":["1 day"],"languages":["English or French"],"maxparticipants":["8"],"minparticipants":["2"],"outcomes":["<p>By the end of this training, you will:<\/p>\r\n<p>\u2705 Understand Git fundamentals and workflows<br data-start=\"3160\" data-end=\"3163\" \/>\u2705 Work confidently with local and remote repositories<br data-start=\"3216\" data-end=\"3219\" \/>\u2705 Use branches and merging strategies effectively<br data-start=\"3268\" data-end=\"3271\" \/>\u2705 Revert, reset, and manage commit history<br data-start=\"3313\" data-end=\"3316\" \/>\u2705 Apply best practices for version control and collaboration<\/p>"],"prerequisites":["<ul>\r\n<li>Basic command-line knowledge (helpful but not required)<\/li>\r\n<li>Familiarity with software development concepts (recommended)<\/li>\